Had Rasheed been available now, Murray might well have called him again but in the event he has made the innovative choice of Amelie Mauresmo as coach, with every match now a sterner test than the last.

Mauresmo spoke on Tuesday for the first time in the tournament, as uncomfortable with the spotlight’s glare as Dimitrov appears to be relishing it. Yet she has enjoyed the work with Murray, who has played sublimely well so far this fortnight.    

‘We are getting to know each other much better and entering more the phase where we can tease each other, we can go a little bit more into details because I’m getting to know his game much better so it is developing the way it is supposed to,’ she said.

